---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout theme="light" showThemeToggle={true} title="Legal | Quincy So">
  <article>
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1>Legal</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Policies, terms, and definitions for Quincy So projects.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- ── GLOSSARY ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <h2>Glossary</h2>
    <dl class="glossary">
      <dt>Operator</dt>
      <dd>The individual or entity responsible for running a service, bot, or website — in this context, Quincy So.</dd>

      <dt>Instance</dt>
      <dd>A specific running copy of software (e.g., a Freesona bot). Different instances may have different operators, configurations, and policies.</dd>

      <dt>Third-Party Service</dt>
      <dd>An external API, platform, or provider used to process requests or deliver functionality. Examples include AI models, hosting providers, and analytics services.</dd>

      <dt>Personal Data</dt>
      <dd>Information that can identify an individual, such as messages, usernames, server IDs, or interaction logs.</dd>

      <dt>Data Retention</dt>
      <dd>How long collected information is stored before being deleted or anonymized.</dd>

      <dt>Service Availability</dt>
      <dd>The uptime and reliability of a service. "As is" means no guarantees are made about continuous operation.</dd>

      <dt>Limitation of Liability</dt>
      <dd>A legal clause stating the operator is not responsible for damages, data loss, or issues arising from use of the service.</dd>

      <dt>Indemnification</dt>
      <dd>Your agreement to hold the operator harmless against claims or damages resulting from your use of the service.</dd>
    </dl>

    <hr />

    <!-- ── Freesona Privacy Policy ──────────────────────────── -->
    <h2>Freesona Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p class="byline">Last Updated: 2026-06-26</p>

    <section class="notice">
      <strong>Project Scope</strong><br />
      This Privacy Policy applies only to Freesona-based bot instances operated by <strong>Quincy So</strong>.
      <br /><br />
      Because Freesona is publicly available, anyone may host their own independent instance with different configurations, logging practices, storage choices, or privacy policies.
      <br /><br />
      If you are interacting with a Freesona-based bot that is not operated by Quincy So, this Privacy Policy does not apply to that instance.
    </section>

    <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
    <p>When you use a Freesona-based bot instance operated by Quincy So, we may collect basic interaction data such as messages sent to the bot, command usage, and server identifiers needed to provide the service. We may also collect diagnostic or error information to improve reliability.</p>

    <h3>2. How We Use Information</h3>
    <p>Collected information is used to operate the bot, respond to requests, enforce rules, debug issues, and improve performance. We do not sell personal data.</p>

    <h3>3. Data Sharing</h3>
    <p>We may share limited data with third-party AI, hosting, or processing providers that are necessary to fulfill your requests. Those providers are subject to their own privacy terms.</p>

    <h3>4. Data Retention</h3>
    <p>We retain data only as long as needed for operation, security, or legal obligations. Where applicable, you may request deletion of your data through the designated support channels.</p>

    <h3>5. Your Choices</h3>
    <p>You may avoid sharing unnecessary information by not using features that require it. Server administrators may also apply their own moderation policies.</p>

    <h3>6. Changes to This Policy</h3>
    <p>This Privacy Policy may be updated at any time. Continued use of the bot means you accept any changes to this policy.</p>

    <h3>7. Contact</h3>
    <p>For questions or privacy-related requests, contact the operator through the designated support channels.</p>

    <div class="notice">
      Continued use of the bot means you accept this Privacy Policy.
    </div>

    <hr />

    <!-- ── Freesona Terms of Service ────────────────────────── -->
    <h2>Freesona Terms of Service</h2>
    <p class="byline">Last Updated: 2026-06-26</p>

    <section class="notice">
      <strong>Definitions</strong><br />
      Throughout this policy:
    </section>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>"The bot"</strong>, <strong>"we"</strong>, and <strong>"us"</strong> refer to the Freesona-based Discord bot and its operator.</li>
      <li><strong>"You"</strong> and <strong>"your"</strong> refer to the Discord user interacting with the bot.</li>
      <li><strong>"Server administrators"</strong> refers to Discord server staff with permission to manage the bot.</li>
      <li><strong>"Third-party services"</strong> refers to external APIs and services used by the bot to process requests.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>1. Overview</h3>
    <p>These Terms of Service explain the rules for using Freesona-based bot instances operated by Quincy So, including acceptable behavior and limitations of the service.</p>
    <p>By using the bot, you agree to these Terms of Service and to the collection and use of data as described in the applicable Privacy Policy.</p>

    <section class="notice">
      <strong>Project Scope</strong><br />
      This bot is based on the public open-source project <strong>Freesona</strong>. These Terms of Service apply only to Freesona-based bot instances operated by <strong>Quincy So</strong>.
      <br /><br />
      Because Freesona is publicly available, anyone may host their own independent instance with different configurations, logging practices, memory systems, hosting providers, or privacy policies.
      <br /><br />
      If you are interacting with a Freesona-based bot that is not operated by Quincy So, these Terms of Service do not apply to that instance.
    </section>

    <h3>2. Use of the Bot</h3>
    <h4>Allowed Use</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Using commands as intended for their stated purposes</li>
      <li>Interacting with the bot within the rules of the server it is deployed in</li>
      <li>Providing feedback or reporting bugs through designated channels</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Prohibited Use</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Spamming, abusing commands, or deliberately triggering excessive API usage</li>
      <li>Attempting to bypass restrictions, inject prompts, or manipulate the AI system</li>
      <li>Using the bot for harassment, hate speech, or any illegal activity</li>
      <li>Using official Sumi branding, identity, or presentation in a misleading or impersonating manner</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. AI-Generated Content</h3>
    <p>Responses generated by this bot may be produced by third-party AI models and external processing services. The bot owner does not guarantee the accuracy, completeness, or appropriateness of AI-generated responses. Do not rely on them for medical, legal, financial, or other professional advice.</p>

    <h3>4. Moderation and Enforcement</h3>
    <p>Server staff and/or the bot owner may restrict or revoke access to the bot at any time if these terms or server rules are violated. Enforcement decisions are final.</p>

    <h3>5. Data Usage</h3>
    <p>Use of the bot involves limited data collection as described in the Privacy Policy above. By using the bot, you also agree to the Privacy Policy.</p>

    <h3>6. Service Availability</h3>
    <p>The bot is provided "as is" with no guarantees of uptime, reliability, or continuous availability. Downtime may occur without notice.</p>

    <h3>7. Changes to the Service</h3>
    <p>Features, commands, or functionality may be modified, suspended, or removed at any time without prior notice. These Terms of Service may also be updated at any time; continued use of the bot constitutes acceptance of any changes.</p>

    <h3>8. Third-Party Services</h3>
    <p>This bot integrates with third-party APIs including Google Gemini, Wolfram Alpha, MVSEP, and others. Use of these services is subject to their respective terms and privacy policies. The bot owner is not responsible for the practices of these third parties.</p>

    <h3>9. Limitation of Liability</h3>
    <p>The bot owner is not responsible for any damages, data loss, or issues resulting from use of the bot, including but not limited to inaccurate AI responses, service interruptions, or unauthorized access.</p>

    <h3>10. Termination</h3>
    <p>Access to the bot may be terminated at any time for any reason, including violations of these terms, at the sole discretion of the bot owner or server staff.</p>

    <h3>11. Contact</h3>
    <p>For concerns, questions, or requests, contact the bot owner through the designated support channels in the server.</p>

    <div class="notice">
      Continued use of the bot means you accept these Terms of Service.
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>